programme.desc: Despite being raised by ninjas, Haru never fits into their clan. But he gets an opportunity to prove his mettle when Sally approaches him to investigate the whereabouts of her criminal boyfriend.

programme.title: Les Miserables
programme.desc: Jean Valjean, an ex-convict who goes on to become the mayor, comes face-to-face with inspector Javert, who is on a quest to nab him for his past deeds.

programme.title: My Girl
programme.desc: Vada, a hypochondriac, becomes distraught when her father, a widower, begins dating Shelly, a makeup artist, and attempts to disrupt their relationship.

programme.title: Stomp The Yard 2: Homecoming
programme.desc: Chance Harris, a young man, tries to find a solution to balance his life, school, work and relationship in order to participate for a national step competition.

programme.title: Excess Baggage

programme.title: Hard Ball
programme.desc: Conor O'Neill strikes a bargain in order to get a loan to pay off his gambling debts. He must coach a Little League baseball team to keep his end of the bargain.

programme.title: T2 Trainspotting

programme.title: Fun With Dick And Jane
programme.desc: When Dick's employer goes bankrupt, he and his wife, Jane, go broke and look for ways to make ends meet. Eventually, they resort to crime and decide to rob a crooked CEO to get their money back.

programme.title: The Whole Nine Yards

programme.title: Lords Of Dogtown
programme.desc: Three young pioneering skateboarders swiftly rise to stardom. However, they soon find their brotherhood threatened as they face different challenges in their personal lives.

programme.title: These Old Broads

programme.title: The Battleship Island
